@startuml

title Agent Invocation - Sequence Diagram

autonumber

actor "Business User" as User
participant "AI Portal" as Portal
participant "Agent Gateway" as Gateway
participant "Agent Runtime" as Runtime
participant "Agent Registry" as Registry
participant "Memory Service" as Memory
participant "Knowledge Service" as Knowledge
participant "Foundation Model" as Model
participant "Evaluation Service" as Evaluation
queue "Kafka" as Kafka
participant "Audit Service" as Audit
participant "Billing Service" as Billing

User -> Portal: Send prompt
Portal -> Gateway: POST /agents/{id}/invoke
Gateway -> Gateway: Authenticate and authorize
Gateway -> Runtime: Route invocation
Runtime -> Registry: Load agent configuration
Registry --> Runtime: Agent config and policies
Runtime -> Memory: Load session context
Memory --> Runtime: Conversation context
Runtime -> Knowledge: Search relevant knowledge
Knowledge --> Runtime: Retrieved chunks and citations
Runtime -> Model: Invoke model with prompt and context
Model --> Runtime: Model response
Runtime -> Evaluation: Queue response evaluation
Runtime -> Kafka: Publish agent.invoked
Runtime --> Gateway: Return answer
Gateway --> Portal: Return response
Portal --> User: Display answer
Kafka -> Audit: Consume agent.invoked
Kafka -> Billing: Consume usage data

@enduml
